{"id":"d=origam-topic-3903//p=5b06e0dbb9b741bfa762adac431bc68e","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3903"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["ad6fc2fad8a04ec7a47840d73965211c"],"__file_part":["823fb94d3d5a4193815fe1be44d5dc84"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["3903"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-create-a-new-project/3903"],"title":["How to create a new Project"],"imagesFound":["8"],"imagesDescribed":["8"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/67b7a84ef5cde384613cc6f6aed790d0bfbe2b21.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1ea78ccf9e98c44e258d1abd98882210f0f4edd0.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e0a90c44b0331fe8548a98198e903804e83040c2.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8225d2672b2547f1b58d26374a4492a62e01d535.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5e678d99d39b2e2eeeb7dcc048dcc8663ccffa62.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/b8ccd692334577beb6811f1d201bc605e0567058.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/6308ac6010e55ef8b78fea27de8b64348d66837c.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/c/c809dc7f4fd45a2ad0a5b51d9ad7171f61b33f44.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# How to create a new Project\n\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-create-a-new-project/3903\n\n@vikter (2025-01-13 09:02:39Z):\n   \n This tutorial will guide you step by step through the process of setting up a new project in ORIGAM Architect. \n \n [!success]- Prerequisites for further work \nTo proceed, you need: \n \n  A running database server  \n \n \n   Run the wizard \n You can find the option to create a new project \u2013 that is, a new application or system \u2013 in the main menu under File. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/67b7a84ef5cde384613cc6f6aed790d0bfbe2b21.png]\nDescription: The image displays a portion of the user interface for ORIGAM Architect, specifically the dropdown menu from the \u0022File\u0022 menu. Visible options include \u0022New Project...\u0022, \u0022Save\u0022 (with shortcut Ctrl\u002BS), \u0022Refresh\u0022 (with shortcut Ctrl\u002BR), \u0022Finish Task\u0022 (with shortcut F5), \u0022Connect,\u0022 \u0022Disconnect,\u0022 \u0022Connection Configuration...,\u0022 \u0022Run Update Scripts...,\u0022 and \u0022Exit.\u0022 The apparent purpose of this interface is to provide users with various functionalities related to project management and connection settings within the ORIGAM Architect environment.\n\n\n  \n When you launch Architect for the first time, the wizard for creating a new project will start automatically. \n   Name your project \n Enter a name for your project. Be sure to choose the name carefully, as changing it later will be very challenging. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1ea78ccf9e98c44e258d1abd98882210f0f4edd0.png]\nDescription: The interface is a dialog window titled \u0022New Project.\u0022 It focuses on entering a project name, indicated by the label \u0022Project Name.\u0022 The field for input is labeled \u0022Name,\u0022 with a default text entry of \u0022MyApplication.\u0022 Below the input field, there is guidance text stating, \u0022Enter a name for your project. It will be used to set the package, database and folders names. Example: MyNewProject.\u0022 At the bottom right, there are two buttons labeled \u0022Next\u0022 and \u0022Cancel,\u0022 suggesting a sequential workflow for project creation. The purpose of the dialog is to set up a new project by collecting the initial name input.\n\n\n  \n   Connect the database \n The next step is to configure the database connection. In this example, we will use an MS SQL server running locally in a Docker container. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e0a90c44b0331fe8548a98198e903804e83040c2.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a user interface for creating a new project involving database configuration, labeled \u0022New Project\u0022 at the top. The section titled \u0022Database\u0022 contains form fields for the following: a dropdown for selecting the \u0022Database\u0022 type, pre-filled with \u0022Microsoft Sql Server,\u0022 a text input for \u0022Database Server\u0022 set to \u0022localhost,\u0022 and a \u0022Port\u0022 field set to \u00221433.\u0022 Additional fields include \u0022User Name,\u0022 with \u0022sa\u0022 filled in, and a \u0022Password\u0022 field represented with asterisks. Below the fields, there are instructional texts advising to enter the database user\u0027s name and password, and that the user must have create database privileges. There are buttons labeled \u0022Next\u0022 and \u0022Cancel\u0022 at the bottom right.\n\n\n  \n You need to enter the username and password that you created when  setting up your database server . If these details are incorrect, you will not be able to complete the creation of the new project. \n \n \nWant to use PostgreSQL? \n In that case, select PostgreSQL as the Database and then later in the already created project, edit the configuration in OrigamSettings.config - Data Connection, both  DataConnectionString  and  DataDataService , plus  DeployPlatforms . In addition to that you need to set the DatabaseType property in the Docker .env file to \u201Cpostgresql\u201C. \n \n   Create app user \n In this step, you will create an account for the first user in your future application. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8225d2672b2547f1b58d26374a4492a62e01d535.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a user interface for creating a new web user within a project application. It includes the title \u0022First Web User\u0022 and a prompt instructing users to fill in details for the first user account. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:37:07"},"vector":[0.017796049,-0.015512902,-0.054041553,0.02085386,-0.010367982,-0.021770686,0.002765749,-0.029236201,0.019656481,0.002451396,0.010661986,-0.02218421,-0.01613938,0.00459819,-0.0037904985,-0.0143605955,0.0028506727,0.01579664,0.07323954,0.03252738,0.015228903,-0.019040179,0.03222382,-0.0035373464,-0.014095305,-0.03123205,0.0058258306,-0.015678804,0.019653333,-0.04248793,0.025248582,-0.07341104,-0.031284593,-0.054608013,0.0013902019,-0.010480695,0.015506084,-0.0039605945,-0.039722778,0.033986814,0.013006508,-0.022121856,-0.01168979,0.01721207,0.034518402,-0.049961027,-0.009894917,0.018405776,0.03317071,-0.020880776,-0.028914394,-0.012287332,0.007859426,-0.028651074,0.028889483,0.06641415,-0.05802194,-0.016071033,-0.06251271,0.016018199,-0.036854398,0.021243464,-0.037243478,-0.027753986,0.003035376,0.03511113,-0.01586307,0.020144878,-0.0078825075,-0.028287427,-0.02878606,0.011614628,-0.0910137,-0.04587906,-0.065865226,0.00037702202,0.042425323,0.020176167,-0.042639576,-0.0002991837,-0.028579967,-0.04091528,0.011728151,-0.0033737905,-0.003381187,-0.0034687785,-0.04087907,0.09460014,-0.0002413211,0.052097503,-0.034000527,-0.03914594,0.043831673,-0.048494183,-0.0025386475,-0.0068646097,0.011919216,0.008616083,-0.013792025,0.032454934,-0.027185522,-0.032387216,-0.04023367,0.005605419,-0.03759671,-0.021702372,0.020303821,-0.044916544,0.0207356,-0.037774127,-0.01468745,-0.022478687,0.040330518,-0.050683387,0.010275712,-0.036752313,-0.0010103362,-0.020452794,-0.0068180137,0.023056189,-0.030320775,0.013502388,0.05678194,-0.001082195,0.009141738,-0.0068231276,-0.046170365,0.010483959,0.008297947,0.04575834,0.058027018,-0.015791463,-0.018959232,0.004169257,-0.030163305,0.031191032,0.0068687755,-0.0041880207,0.0091493055,-0.008638961,0.054575283,0.0005906643,0.0067865904,-0.055868577,0.031420894,-0.02834